President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has ordered that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff as a mark of respect for the victims of the violence that occurred on May 6, 2023, in Allen, Texas. This order applies to the White House, public buildings and grounds, military posts and naval stations, naval vessels of the Federal Government, and all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad. The flag will be flown at half-staff until sunset on May 11, 2023. This proclamation was made on May 7, 2023.